Start
/ Compile one step. Planner gave us the set of actions involved via planStep.actions;
/ the compiler decides chain order, fills parameters, and emits the .pr actions array.
/ Retry semantics are delegated to error.handle (built-in RetryCount, GoalFirst order).

- set %step% = %goal.Steps[planStep.index]%
- call Compile


Compile
/ Validate planner's action set against runtime catalog + augment with explicit
/ module.action tokens from step text. Drops hallucinated entries; appends any
/ literal `module.action` mention the planner missed. See building-the-build.md
/ "preventing self-rebuild corruption" for the rationale.
- build.validateStepActions step=%step%, actions=%planStep.actions%, write to %planStep.actions%
- set %actions% = %!app.module.action.list%
- where %actions% Name in %planStep.actions%, write to %actions%
- build.types actions=%planStep.actions%, write to %typeInfo%
/ Per-step so the snapshot reflects the Actions just written by prior BuildSteps.
- goal.getTypes Goal=%goal%, write to %varTypes%
- set %stepVarTypes% = %varTypes[step.Index]%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/templates/stepForLlm.template", write to %stepForLlm%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/templates/stepActionDetails.template", write to %actionDetails%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/Compile.llm", write to %buildStepPrompt%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/CompileUser.llm", write to %buildStepUserMsg%
- set %messages% = [{"Role":"system", "Content":"%buildStepPrompt%"}, {"Role":"user", "Content":"%buildStepUserMsg%"}]
/ QueryAndVerify wraps llm.query + a missing-actions check (throws on missing-actions).
/ on error key="missing-actions": run RefineActions first (expands %planStep.actions%),
/ then retry the whole QueryAndVerify. RetryCount is the runtime's job, no counter.
- call QueryAndVerify, on error key "missing-actions" call RefineActions, then retry 2 times

/ system prompt is stashed once at goal level (%trace.compileSystem%) — do not duplicate it here.
- add {goal: %goal.Name%, index: %step.Index%, stepText: %step.Text%, actions: %planStep.actions%, user: %buildStepUserMsg%, response: %compileResult%, rawResponse: %compileResult!RawResponse%, usage: {model: %compileResult.Model%, promptTokens: %compileResult.PromptTokens%, cachedTokens: %compileResult.CachedTokens%, completionTokens: %compileResult.CompletionTokens%, totalTokens: %compileResult.TotalTokens%, cost: %compileResult.Cost%, cached: %compileResult.Cached%}} to %trace.stepPasses%

- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Actions% = %compileResult.actions%
- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Formal% = %compileResult.formal%

/ Validation retry: FixValidation re-queries the LLM with the validator's complaint as
/ previousConversation context, writes the corrected compileResult, updates goal.Steps.
/ Then retry build.validate against the corrected actions.
- build.validate actions=%goal.Steps[step.Index].Actions%, on error call FixValidation, then retry 2 times

- call EmitSummary


QueryAndVerify
- llm.query Messages=%messages%, Schema={formal: string, actions: list<{module: string, action: string, parameters?: list<{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}>, errors?: list<{key: string, message: string}>}>, confidence: string, explanation?: string, errors?: list<{key: string, message: string}>}, cache=%!build.cache%, on error call HandleStepFailure, write to %compileResult%
- if %compileResult.errors[0].key% is "missing-actions", throw error "missing-actions: %compileResult.errors[0].message%" key="missing-actions"


RefineActions
/ Planner continuation: hand the LLM the compiler's complaint, get an expanded action set.
- set %complaint% = "Compiler returned missing-actions for step %step.Index% (text: '%step.Text%'). Current action set is insufficient: %planStep.actions%. Reason: %!error.Message%. Return a corrected action set for step %step.Index% only. Include `confidence` (VeryHigh|High|Medium|Low|VeryLow) and `explanation` (one short sentence when confidence is Medium or below) — recovery confidence matters because it tells the dev whether even the correction is a guess.", type=string
- set %refineMessages% = [{"Role":"user", "Content":"%complaint%"}]- llm.query Messages=%refineMessages%, Schema={index: int, actions: list<string>, confidence: string, explanation?: string}, cache=%!build.cache%, previousConversation=%plan%, write to %correction%
- set %planStep.actions% = %correction.actions%
- set %trace.plan.steps[step.Index].actions% = %correction.actions%
- call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="step-missing-actions", step=%step%


FixValidation
/ Validator rejected the compiled actions. Re-prompt the LLM with the validator's
/ complaint, write corrected compileResult, update goal.Steps so the subsequent retry
/ of build.validate sees the corrected actions.
- set %fixMessages% = [{"Role":"user", "Content":"Your previous response was rejected by the validator: %!error.Message%\n\nReturn the corrected response in the same Output Shape (formal, actions, confidence, explanation, errors, warnings) for this step only. Include `confidence` (VeryHigh|High|Medium|Low|VeryLow) and `explanation` (one short sentence when confidence is Medium or below) — recovery confidence matters because it tells the dev whether even the correction is a guess."}]- llm.query Messages=%fixMessages%, Schema={formal: string, actions: list<{module: string, action: string, parameters?: list<{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}>, modifiers?: list<{module: string, action: string, parameters?: list<{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}>}>, errors?: list<{key: string, message: string}>}>, confidence: string, explanation?: string, errors?: list<{key: string, message: string}>}, cache=%!build.cache%, previousConversation=%compileResult%, write to %compileResult%
- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Actions% = %compileResult.actions%
- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Formal% = %compileResult.formal%
- call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="step-validation-error", step=%step%, errorMessage=%!error.Message%


HandleStepFailure
- call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="step-build-error", step=%step%, errorMessage=%!error.Message%
- throw %!error%


EmitSummary
/ Per-step build summary line, plus a warning line when either the planner or
/ the compiler reported Low / VeryLow confidence (LLM had to settle for a
/ fallback action or guess a mapping — the dev should see it at build time).
- if %compileResult.Cached% is true, call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="step-cached", step=%step%
- if %compileResult.Cached% is not true, call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="step-fresh", step=%step%
- if %planStep.confidence% is "Low", call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="confidence-warning-planner", planStep=%planStep%
- if %planStep.confidence% is "VeryLow", call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="confidence-warning-planner", planStep=%planStep%
- if %compileResult.confidence% is "Low", call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="confidence-warning-compiler", compileResult=%compileResult%
- if %compileResult.confidence% is "VeryLow", call /system/builder/EmitBuildEvent kind="confidence-warning-compiler", compileResult=%compileResult%
